  "response": "# Verdict: REVISE\n\n**Overall Assessment**: The BuggyFileInput component has critical accessibility design gaps in label association, error communication, and state announcement. The file input lacks a proper label, error messages aren't programmatically associated, and validation state isn't communicated to assistive technology.\n\n**Pre-commitment Predictions**: \n- Missing label association (div instead of label)\n- Error message not associated via aria-describedby\n- Missing aria-invalid on invalid state\n- No help text for file type restrictions\n\n**Critical Findings** (blocks access):\n1. **Missing label association**: \n   - File: `BuggyFileInput.jsx:12` (input element)\n   - User group: Screen reader users\n   - WCAG 1.3.1 (Info and Relationships)\n   - Fix: Replace \"Upload file\" div with `<label htmlFor=\"file-input\">` and add `id=\"file-input\"` to input\n\n2. **Error message not associated**:\n   - File: `BuggyFileInput.jsx:17` (error message div)\n   - User group: Screen reader users\n   - WCAG 1.3.1 (Info and Relationships)\n   - Fix: Add `aria-describedby=\"error-message\"` to input and `id=\"error-message\"` to error div\n\n**Major Findings** (significantly degrades experience):\n1. **Missing aria-invalid**:\n   - File: `BuggyFileInput.jsx:12` (input element)\n   - User group: Screen reader users\n   - WCAG 4.1.2 (Name, Role, Value)\n   - Fix: Add `aria-invalid={error ? 'true' : 'false'}` to input\n\n2. **Missing help text for file types**:\n   - File: `BuggyFileInput.jsx:12` (input element)\n   - User group: All users\n   - WCAG 3.3.2 (Labels or Instructions)\n   - Fix: Add `aria-describedby=\"file-hint\"` to input and add `<div id=\"file-hint\">Allowed: PDF, DOC, DOCX (max 5MB)</div>`\n\n**What's Missing**:\n- Missing label association between \"Upload file\" text and input\n- Missing error message association to input\n- Missing validation state communication via aria-invalid\n- Missing help text for file type restrictions\n\n**Multi-Perspective Notes**:\n- **Screen reader user**: Would hear \"Upload file\" but not know it's associated with the input. Error message would be announced only if focus lands on it directly.\n- **Keyboard-only user**: Can tab to input but won't know about file type restrictions or errors without visual inspection.\n- **Low vision user**: Error message may be hard to see without proper contrast and focus indicators.\n- **Cognitive accessibility**: Error message is unclear without knowing which input it refers to.\n\n**Verdict Justification**: The component fails to communicate essential information to assistive technology users. The missing label association and error communication create a complete access barrier for screen reader users. The missing help text for file types violates WCAG 3.3.2. These issues require immediate revision before the component can be considered accessible.\n\n**Open Questions**:\n- Should the error message use aria-live=\"polite\" for better announcement timing?\n- Does the error message need to include the error type (e.g., \"Error: File too large\") for clarity?",
